TRL2 is a type of Technology Readiness Level, which is also known as TRL. It is categorized as something that only achieves success in applied research and must have TRL 2.
TRL3 is a type of Technology Readiness Level and is also referred to as TRL. It is characterized by the successful proof of concept. Moreover, it must achieve a TRL of 3.

TRL4, which stands for Technology Readiness Level 4, is a specific type of TRL that signifies a technology has only succeeded in a laboratory environment. Additionally, it implies that something must attain TRL 4 status.

TRL5 is a type of Technology Readiness Level (TRL), which is categorized as something that only achieves success in a representative environment. Additionally, TRL5 is a requirement that must be met for this specific level.

TRL6 is a type of Technology Readiness Level, which is a classification within the broader category of TRL. It is distinguished as a type that only achieves success in an end-to-end environment. Moreover, TRL6 is a type that must have TRL 6 characteristics.

TRL7 is a type of Technology Readiness Level, which is a classification within the broader category of TRLs. It is specifically characterized as something that has achieved success in an operational environment and fundamentally requires attaining TRL 7 status.

TRL8 is a type of TRL, which stands for Technology Readiness Level. It is specifically associated with technologies that have found success in a verified and validated environment. Additionally, for a technology to be classified under TRL8, it must meet the criteria of TRL 8.

TRL9 is a type of TRL, which stands for Technology Readiness Level. It is identified as a type that only achieves success in a mission-tested environment. Furthermore, it is mandated that TRL9 must have TRL 9.
